{
  "texts": [
    "This outcome is expected due to the large full width at half maximum (FWHM), which limits the observation of small-scale CMB polarization.",
    "Consequently, a significant reconstruction noise in the lensing potential occurs, degrading the delensing process.Combining the 0.8m-gSAT with 6m-gLAT further enhances delensing by removing an additional 25% of the lensing B-modes.",
    "This combination effectively reduces the FWHM, thereby decreasing the noise in the lensing potential as shown in Fig. 4 and improving the signal-to-noise ratio in the observed CMB maps.Future satellite experiments, as described in the paper, are able to provide a high signal-to-noise ratio on scales at ℓ < 3000.",
    "This results in a high signal-to-noise ratio in the reconstruction of ϕ, which is a major factor in the construction of the lensing template and the delensing procedure.",
    "These experiments can remove approximately 80% of the lensing B-modes using either of the two delensing methods.Compared to Fig. 7, the values of the delensing fractions are greatly reduced by approximately 10% to 20% for the two methods in each experiment."
  ]
}